This paper deals with the construction and release of a multi-domain and multi-modality event dataset, which involves natural language processing (NLP) for textual news articles, information retrieval (IR) for collecting data from different news media sites, computer vision (CV) for image posts shared on Flickr social media, multimedia (MM) for annotating the dataset with different contributors, and machine learning (ML) for exploring the problem of transferring event knowledge obtained from one data domain to heterogeneous data domain. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), followed by cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
